keywords assemble
---
Syntax: assemble <piece1> <piece2>

Assembles two compatible item pieces into a single complete object. Both
items must be PIECE-type objects that reference each other as matching
components. When successfully assembled, both piece items are consumed and
replaced with the completed object in your inventory.

A piece item's description will usually indicate what it combines with.
The resulting object is created at your current level.

Example:
  assemble hilt blade
  -- If "hilt" and "blade" are matching pieces, they combine into a sword.

Restrictions:
  - Both items must be in your inventory.
  - Both items must be of the PIECE item type.
  - The pieces must be specifically designed to combine with each other.

See also: inventory get put
